\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "sec: keyswap2"

\end_inset

).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The next three keyboard options relate to the option links.
 PCW keyboards have three option links, and by default none of these links
 are connected.
 To my knowledge no PCW software uses the links, but for completeness JOYCE
 allows you to connect them here.
 The only one with a noticeable effect is LK2; if it's connected, pressing
 the Shift key will not cancel Shift Lock.
 For details of what LK1 and LK3 do, see the PCW hardware guide.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
There are also two joystick options.
 These relate to a curious little piece of history.
 The controllers in all PCW keyboards include joystick support; but there's
 no joystick socket for them to plug in to (compare the PC1512 keyboard,
 where there is a joystick socket).
 Strictly in the interests of completeness, JOYCE provides the joystick
 sockets.
 To activate one or the other, select 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Joystick 1
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

