\emph on
b f
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
or: 
\end_layout

\begin_layout LyX-Code
XPALETTE 
\emph on
br bg bb fr fg fb
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
XPALETTE takes advantage of the colours on a VGA screen to allow the PCW
 to display in any colour scheme, not just black and white.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The version with two parameters works the same way as on a CPC or a Spectrum
 +3 (though neither of these has as many colours as JOYCE has).
 For example, on a CPC you might type:
\end_layout

\begin_layout LyX-Code
PALETTE 2 63
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
to get white text on a blue background.
 So, in JOYCE, type
\end_layout

\begin_layout LyX-Code
XPALETTE 2 63
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
and the screen colours obediently change.
\end_layout

